Fisherman: "My butt itchy."
Narrator: "The fishermen wonder whether climate change is to blame for that too".

@upstreamer 97-98% of scientists around the world, from the U.N. to NASA to NOAA, agree there is man-made climate change. Countless scientific studies, reviews and organizations make this completely clear and solid. "It is unequivocal"--the first three words of the latest U.N. report.  You want to pretend almost 100% of scientists from every credo and country are all corrupt, every one of them politicized in exactly the same way, to all come up with exactly the same scientific results? 
Also, do you not watch the news, do you not see with your own eyes all the increased wildfires, droughts, floods, melting ice caps, hurricanes and typhoons and monsoons, heat extremes, rising sea levels, coastal inundations? All of these are quantifiable and proven, and available on handy graphs and maps so you can see how it's all getting so much worse. If Kiribati were an isolated case, then fine, maybe it's because stupid politicians destroyed some of the mangrove swamps. But it's the opposite of an isolated case, it is but one of countless examples in a global pattern. Many other places around the world are also submerging, and they're not little-known tiny atolls with small populations. Several of them are coastal cities with very large populations: "So-called 'delta cities' are already bearing the brunt of rising seas. More than 340 million people live in deltas like Miami, New York City, New Orleans, Tokyo, Hong Kong, Melbourne, Rotterdam, Venice, Dhaka, Guangzhou, Ho Chi Minh City, and Manila." Pretty sure all those mega cities aren't flooding because some politicians cut down some mangroves. 
For now they're protecting themselves with technology, and some of them can probably keep the water at bay with high-engineering infrastructure, like Rotterdam. But most of them are projected to lose the fight and end up underwater, some within our lifetime--especially since climate deniers such as yourself fabricate all kinds of fallacious and false pretexts to keep belching greenhouse gases into the atmosphere--the very atmosphere that keeps life on Earth alive.

So, when it's later discovered that mankind is contributing little (if any) to global warming, maybe resources (read: money) will stop being wasted on the Al Gores of the world. In reality, to stop global warming, we'd have to:
1) Correct the 'wobble' in earth's rotation;
2) Correct the earth's slightly erratic orbit around the sun;
3) Find a way to manipulate crustal and oceanic plate tectonics, and;
4) Find a way to manipulate oceanic currents.


Let me know when someone's figured even ONE of these out.

